[This line](https://github.com/GarageGames/Torque3D/blob/development/Engine/source/core/util/tSignal.h#L57) causes compiler warnings from `gcc`. So many warnings. It also seems to be incorrect. The context is:

```
SignalBase()
{
   mList.next = mList.prev = &mList;
   mList.order = 0.5f;
   mTriggerNext = NULL;
}
```

But `mTriggerNext` has type `Vector<DelegateLink*>`. What was the intent behind this assignment, and can we replace it with code that doesn't cause an error?

